# Privacy Policy — Còcaidh Creamed

**Last updated:** March 2026

## Summary
Còcaidh Creamed does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data whatsoever.

## Data Collection
This extension collects **no data**. It does not:
- Track browsing history
- Collect or transmit the URLs you visit
- Store any identifiers or usage statistics
- Connect to any external servers or APIs
- Use analytics or crash reporting services

## Permissions Explained
The extension requests the following permissions, solely to perform its stated function:

| Permission | Why it's needed |
|---|---|
| `cookies` | To read and delete cookies for the current site |
| `storage` | To save your extension preferences (stored locally on your device only) |
| `activeTab` | To determine which site you're currently on |
| `scripting` | To clear localStorage and sessionStorage by injecting a short-lived script into the current tab |
| `contextMenus` | To add a right-click menu option |
| `host_permissions` (http/https) | Required by Chrome to access and delete cookies across sites |

## Local Storage Only
The only data stored by this extension is your own settings (e.g. whether auto-reload is enabled). This is saved in Chrome's `storage.local` API, which means it stays on your device and is never transmitted anywhere.

## Contact
If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please open an issue on the project repository.
